Black land "planted" agricultural modernization - Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency, Harbin, July 26, by wire: Black land "planted" agricultural modernization
In the height of summer, two pharmaceutical spraying aircraft skimmed the 10,000-acre high-yield demonstration field at the second operation station of the Fifth Management Area of Friendship Farm, forming two white lines. The large letters "the first field in the world" planted with black rice seedlings in the green field stood out.
Kong Lingqiang, the station manager of the operation station, said that the aircraft can spray medicine on more than 6,000 mu of arable land a day, which is about eight times more efficient than drones and hundreds of times more manual.
This farm is located in Friendship County, Heilongjiang Province, the largest grain producing province in China. From the sound of "Shua Shua" rice cutting in the past to the sound of "rumble" today, traditional Chinese farming and farms have achieved metamorphosis in this black soil belt.
In addition to aircraft, satellites are also used in the modern agricultural production of Friendship Farm.
Kong Lingqiang introduced that on the one hand, they use satellite remote sensing technology to achieve precise fertilization, reduce agricultural inputs and reduce pollution. On the other hand, satellite navigation technology can improve the level of standardized operation of agricultural machinery in the field.
In the process of rice production this year, the farm expanded the operating area of satellite navigation unmanned transplanting technology from 3,000 mu last year to 30,000 mu.
This technology makes seedling planting more uniform, maximizes the utilization of sunlight and cultivated land resources, and saves 16 yuan in labor costs per acre.
Farms have tried new technologies such as informatization and intelligentization in agricultural production, forming the largest agricultural machinery group in China from the ground to the sky.
According to statistics, at present, the total number of agricultural machinery on farms is 49,000 units (pieces), and the comprehensive mechanization rate in the fields has reached 99.8%.
Agricultural machinery operations achieve 100% GPS satellite navigation, 100% precision sowing in dry fields and 100% high-powered locomotives in dry fields.
"Green agriculture, smart agriculture and digital agriculture are the exploration direction of agricultural modernization."
Liu Hualian, director of Friendship Farm, said.
The key to agricultural modernization lies in scientific and technological progress.
In recent years, Heilongjiang Agricultural Reclamation, represented by farms, has played a demonstration and leading role in the demonstration and leading role of modern large agricultural "aircraft carriers", and has initially established a modern agricultural industry system led by large-scale planting, standardized production and industrial management.
On the outskirts of Friendship County, there is an agricultural machinery Expo Park covering an area of 350,000 square meters.
Here, more than 140 agricultural machinery and equipment introduced and used by Heilongjiang Agricultural Reclamation over the years are on display.
These agricultural machinery and farms have witnessed the development of agricultural modernization in China.
Xie Xiaojia for everyone - People of different ethnic groups in Jiangkou River Union, Hefei, Anhui Province, transfer direct attack - Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency, Hefei, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Xie Xiaojia for everyone - People of all ethnic groups in the Jiangkou River Union of Hefei, Anhui Province, have transferred direct attacks
Xinhua News Agency reporters Chen Shangying, Wang Liwu, Liu Xia Cun
On July 25, at about 4 p.m., Fu Kunbao, wearing muddy rubber shoes, went from the front house to the back room and went back and forth with his wife, Zhou Yan, busy packing up their things.
"When I received a phone call from village cadres to transfer, I was still cutting grass in the field."
Fu Kunbao said that he transferred more than 60 acres of land and grew rice, which is now growing well. "He also took medicine yesterday, and his tools and everything have not been cleaned up."
Fu Kunbao pointed to the pesticide sprayer placed in the corner. "No one wants their home to be flooded. Give up their small home for everyone."
In order to cope with the persistent high water level pressure and possible heavy rainfall in Chaohu Lake, the city of Hefei, Anhui Province, is ready to open the flood diversion water storage of Jiangkou River Union County, where Fu Kunbaojia is located, on the 26th.
Jiangkou River Lianwei is located in Feixi County, next to Chaohu levee.
There are thousands of villagers involved in Yan Dian Township and Sanhe Township who need to be transferred.
As of 1600 hours on the 25th, the water level of Chaohu Lake, the fifth largest freshwater lake in China, remained at a high of 13.2 meters, 0.7 meters above the guaranteed water level.
The kitchen of Fu Kunbao 's house is clean. There is a pot of pumpkin head vegetables on the table. There are also eggs and some brine vegetables in the fridge.
"I didn 't expect to move. The water of the Jiangkou River is looking good at present."
Zhou Yan said that the home is a bungalow, and some large objects have not yet been put where for the time being.
"Pack up the valuable items first. Refrigerators and televisions, which are large pieces, can be put in the homes of neighbors or relatives on high ground for the time being."
Wang Li, a village cadre, gave Fu Kunbao advice.
Wang Lizheng is responsible for the transfer and resettlement of 13 villagers, and one family notifies each family to confirm the resettlement plan for each person.
The closest settlement to Fu Kunbao 's family is Su Xiaoxue, Yan Dian Township, about 2 kilometers away.
In addition to large pieces, Fu Kunbao and his wife also have a headache of more than 1,000 jin of grain and some newly bought furniture in the family.
"The grain is ready to be dragged to relatives' homes. There is no way to move the furniture."
As soon as the couple discussed, they put a stool under the newly bought bed and raised the bed by about half a meter.
At 6 p.m., Fu Kunbao began to use a tricycle to transport things to relatives' homes, and Zhou Yan continued to clean up at home.
More than 11 p.m., the couple looked at it before and after at home, pulled on the electric gate and prepared to go to the settlement.
"I hope the water will return early."
Fu Kunbao said.
On July 26, at 9.30am, the reporter saw at the scene of Jiangkou River Union County that the local area had made all preparations before flood diversion.
