Church fire in Nantes, France: Parish volunteers admit to arson and are usually kind and taciturn - CNN
On July 26, according to foreign media, on July 18, the famous Cathedral of St. Peter and St. Paul, a gem of religious history in Nantes, France, was severely damaged in a fire, and the large organ was completely destroyed.
On the 26th local time, the Nantes prosecutor announced that a parish volunteer who was responsible for the security of the cathedral had been charged with "arson and destruction".
He has admitted that he set the fire in the church himself.
According to the report, local prosecutor Senas said that the 39-year-old parish volunteer from Rwanda admitted that he set fire to three places in the cathedral at night.
The man's lawyer said that the arsonist now regrets doing such a thing.
A few years ago, this person entered France through the means of asylum. He was sheltered in the diocese where the fire occurred and taken in in the church.
The prosecution pointed out that recently, he tried to renew his visa and was in the process of talking and communicating with the police station about it.
However, the church said it still could not believe that the usually very kind, smiling, but not very talkative believer would destroy the church he loved so much.
On the day of the fire on July 18, the volunteer had already been questioned and investigated by the police because of illogical problems in his account, but he was later released.
The picture shows firefighters carrying out rescue efforts at the scene.
On the evening of the 25th, the man was arraigned again because the professional engineers of the laboratory of the Central Police Department in Paris obtained new evidence.
This time, the man admitted to setting the fire himself.
It is reported that if convicted of intentional arson and destruction, the suspect may face 10 years in prison and a fine of 150,000 euros.
According to the report, the fire caused serious damage to the Cathedral of St. Pierre and St. Paul. The organ in the church was completely destroyed and the stained glass window behind the organ was also badly damaged.
According to Brunet, the chief architect of French historical conservation buildings, it is conservatively estimated that the restoration of Nantes Cathedral will take at least three years.
Comprehensive news: American unilateralism undermines bilateral relations. International public opinion supports China's countermeasure against the United States - Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, July 26 (Xinhua) -- On the morning of July 24, the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs informed the US Embassy in China that China had decided to revoke the establishment and operation license of the US Consulate General in Chengdu and put forward specific requirements for the Consulate General to stop all business and activities.
International public opinion believes that the unilateralist measures taken by the United States have caused serious distress to the bilateral relations between China and the United States. China has responded to the unreasonable provocations of the United States side, and it is legitimate and necessary to take countermeasures.
Andres Borks, director of the Center for Chinese Studies at the Institute of International Studies at the University of Chile, said that the unilateralist measures of the United States have destroyed the bridge of understanding between the Chinese and American peoples and caused a crisis in the relations between the two great powers.
China informed the United States that the closure of its Consulate General in Chengdu is a countermeasure to the unilateral measures of the United States and is in line with diplomatic practice.
Patricio Justo, a professor at the Argentine Catholic University and director of the Arab-China Research Center, believes that China's above decision is a legitimate and necessary countermeasure to the previous provocations of the United States and is not aimed at ordinary American people.
The United States is trying to divert the attention of the American people by pressuring China to cover up its poor response to the new crown epidemic.
Bambang Suryono, chairman of the Asian Innovation Research Center, an Indonesian think tank, said that the provocative diplomatic posture adopted by the United States has caused serious distress to the bilateral relations between China and the United States, which are facing serious challenges.
China's notification to the United States that the closure of its Consulate General in Chengdu is a normal countermeasure, in line with diplomatic practice, and reflects not only China's principled position of resolutely safeguarding its own interests, but also the rational and beneficial nature of China's diplomacy.
Tanzanian current affairs commentator Francis Semwenza said that China's above decision is a legitimate and necessary response to the provocation of the United States.
In order for China-US relations to return to normal, the US side should take the initiative to improve its relations with China and stop interfering in China's internal affairs.
The United States should focus on how to achieve win-win results with China economically and politically, and how to benefit the two peoples and the international community as a whole.
Ali Youssef, Executive Director of the Sudan-based Federation of Arab Indigenous Chinese Friendship Associations, said that the countermeasures forced by China are a legitimate and necessary response to the unreasonable behavior of the United States side, in line with international law and the basic norms of international relations, as well as diplomatic practices.
Previously, the United States called for the closure of the Chinese Consulate General in Houston, which seriously violated international law and the basic norms of international relations.
It is hoped that the United States will revoke the previous relevant decisions and create the necessary conditions for the return of bilateral relations to normal.
Singapore's Lianhe Zaobao newspaper published an editorial saying that the greater strategic intention of the United States is to encircle China and prevent its continued rise.
In the face of the pressing of the United States, although China is very reluctant to see China-US relations continue to deteriorate, it has to take countermeasures.
