Xinhua News Agency, Guangzhou, July 26 (Xinhua) -- A reporter learned from the Guangdong Maritime Police Bureau that recently, the Bureau, in conjunction with the Guangzhou Customs and Public Security Department, knocked out a huge refined oil smuggling gang. It was preliminarily verified that the gang had smuggled about 120,000 tons of refined oil products since 2019, with a case value of about 800 million yuan and tax evasion of about 240 million yuan.
The Guangdong Maritime Police Bureau and the customs anti-smuggling department jointly gradually mapped out the personnel division and organizational structure of the gang.
