Jiangxi opens up a "green channel" for young people on the front line of flood control to enlist in the army - Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency, Nanchang, July 26 (Guo Dongming, Xiong Liang) The conscription office of the Jiangxi Provincial People's Government recently made it clear that priority shall be given to individuals or their children who have performed outstanding in this flood rescue and relief task who meet the conditions for conscription and have passed both medical and political examinations.
"After the registration of the conscripts, we will give priority to the appointment of soldiers after verification by the community where the conscripts are located, the Street Armed Forces Department and the Shuyang District Conscription Office."
Wang Hui, Vice Minister of the Ministry of People 's Armed Forces of Shuyang District of Jiujiang City, said that affected by the flood, they concentrated on organizing medical examinations for young applicants for three days starting on the 25th.
Zhou Jingfan, a young conscript in Shuyang District of Jiujiang City, is a 22-year-old college graduate. His mother is a community worker and his father is a veteran of a department of the Air Force. Zhou Jingfan 's parents have been on duty on the front line of flood control and flood fighting for ten days.
"These days, I see in the news that the people's soldiers are desperate to defend their hometown on the front line of flood control. I also want to be like them."
Zhou Jingfan said that he had a dream of joining the army since he was a child, and through this flood fighting, he strengthened his determination to join the military camp.
Jiujiang City also regards flood rescue and rescue as a "living textbook" for conscription publicity. Taking the community as the unit, they called on young conscripts to voluntarily participate in the tasks of patrolling and checking embankments and guarding duty. They now understand the nature and purpose of the people's army and strengthen their confidence in joining the army and reporting to the country.
Luo Jiuyu, commissar of the Ministry of People 's Armed Forces of Shuyang District of Jiujiang City, said that by giving priority to the appointment of soldiers, he hoped to inspire more young conscripts and create a good social atmosphere in which it is honorable to participate in the task and honorable to join the army.
