Upgraded version of Russian helicopter gunship card - 52M first out of factory at the end of the year - Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency Moscow, July 25 (Xinhua) -- According to the plan of the Russian Ministry of Defense, the Ka-52M, an upgraded version of the Russian helicopter gunship (hereinafter referred to as Wuzhi) Ka-52, will be completed and replaced for the first time in December this year. The model will be greatly improved in reconnaissance, communications and weapons performance.
According to a recent report in Russia's Yediot newspaper, Wuzhika-52M is called the "Super Alligator". Its development contract was signed by the Russian military and military industrial units in April last year. At present, the first two upgraded Wuzhi are undergoing renovation and replacement at the Far East Helicopter Manufacturing Plant of the Russian "Progress" Aerospace Group Corporation. Its state-level testing and improvement finishing work will be completed by October 2022.
According to Russian experts with knowledge of the above upgrade work, the Wuzhika-52, the "predecessor" of the "super alligator", was officially installed in November 2011. The model exposed some weaknesses in its use. This upgrade is precisely for the purpose of "filling the short board".
The report said that compared with the Ka-52, the Ka-52M will be partially equipped with new protective materials that do not add weight. Its pilot cockpit will be strengthened and equipped with new equipment to withstand missile attacks, thus increasing the probability of battlefield survival. It will be equipped with more powerful generators in order to power more complex airborne electronic equipment. The photoelectric system will be upgraded to be able to detect and identify battlefield targets further apart. The new light multi-purpose missile, which mainly attacks armored combat vehicles and reinforced concrete fortifications, will have a range of up to 20 kilometers.
In addition, the Ka-52M will have more advanced electronic guidance systems, weapons targeting systems and navigation equipment.
Russian experts also said that it is worth noting that the Ka-52M will be equipped with communication equipment to communicate with drones, so as to obtain information transmitted by nearby drones in real time in the air, such as displaying images taken by drones on the cockpit screen of the helicopter.
It is planned that the pilots of the Ka-52M can directly control the drones with which they cooperate, thus improving the pilots' grasp of the battlefield situation and guidance of long-range missiles.
According to Russian media reports, Russian Deputy Minister of Defense Klitschko said in December last year that the Russian Ministry of Defense plans to purchase more than 110 Vuzhika-52M by 2027.
