Hebei has rehydrated 1.75 billion cubic meters of rivers and lakes ecologically since the beginning of this year -- ScienceDaily
Xinhua News Agency, Shijiazhuang, July 26 (Reporter Wang Kun) A reporter learned from the Hebei Provincial Water Resources Department that since the beginning of this year, Hebei Province has made overall use of the diversion of river water and local reservoir water, and has successively implemented ecological water recharge to 28 rivers, including Hutuo River, Tanghe River and Yuma River, as well as Baiyangdian, completing a total of 1.75 billion cubic meters of ecological water recharge to rivers and lakes.
Hebei Province has seized the favorable opportunity of the South-to-North Water diversion Central Line project to increase the flow and transmission of water, and has implemented ecological water recharge by using the diversion of river water to rivers such as the Tanghe, Shahe and Shilong rivers.
At the same time, nine large and medium-sized reservoirs, including the Western Ocean and Dongwushi, as well as Baiyangdian, have been used to implement ecological water recharge to Shuyang River and Qinglong River, with a cumulative surface area of more than 90 square kilometers.
In order to do a good job in ecological water recharge, the Hebei Provincial Water Resources Department has actively organized and carried out the work of detecting, rectifying and strengthening hidden dangers of water recharge rivers and cleaning river channels, refining practical measures and strengthening inspection, management and protection.
Through supervision and inspection and centralized unannounced visits, all kinds of problems are solved in a timely manner, ensuring the safety and order of river water recharge.
According to the relevant person in charge of the Hebei Provincial Water Resources Department, the orderly implementation of ecological water recharge in rivers and lakes has effectively repaired the ecological environment of rivers and lakes in Hebei Province, promoted the recharge and conservation of groundwater along the coast, greatly improved the living environment and economic development environment along the route, and is of great significance for achieving the goal of "clear water, green shore, smooth river and beautiful scenery" management and protection of rivers and lakes.
