For the first time, the United States launched a countervailing investigation against China for "undervaluation of the renminbi exchange rate"
In response to the recent announcement by the US Department of Commerce, it has decided to launch an anti-dumping countervailing investigation against strap (strap) products originating in China and launch an investigation on the "undervaluation of the RMB exchange rate" project.
China's Ministry of Commerce pointed out that this is the first time that the United States has opened a case to investigate the so-called "undervaluation of the RMB exchange rate" project in a countervailing case, which China firmly opposes.
China's Ministry of Commerce issued a special press release in this regard on the evening of the 23rd, saying that China implements a managed floating exchange rate system based on market supply and demand, adjusted with reference to a basket of currencies, and that the market plays a decisive role in the formation of the exchange rate.
The press release stressed that, in general, the RMB exchange rate is at a reasonable equilibrium level and is not undervalued.
Since 2005, the RMB has appreciated cumulatively against the US dollar by more than 17%.
According to the data released by the Bank for International Settlements, from the beginning of 2005 to May 2020, the effective exchange rate of the renminbi name appreciated by 38% and the real effective exchange rate appreciated by 49%, making it the strongest currency in the G20 economy and one of the largest currencies in the world.
The Ministry of Commerce pointed out that the exchange rate issue exceeds the authority of members to conduct countervailing investigations in accordance with the rules of the World Trade Organization.
In February this year, the United States amended its regulations to conduct countervailing investigations against the exchange rates of other countries. It has been suspected of violating the WTO rules and has been opposed by many parties.
According to the press release, even in accordance with US regulations, there are a large number of errors in the content of the applicant 's complaint, which does not have the necessary countervailing elements such as financial assistance, benefit granting and exclusivity.
China urges the United States to abide by existing international rules and stop conducting countervailing investigations into the so-called "undervaluation of the RMB exchange rate".
Affected by the further rise in tensions between China and the United States, the offshore and onshore RMB exchange rates against the US dollar fell sharply during the session on the 22nd, both falling below the 7.0 yuan mark against the US dollar.
It is worth paying attention to whether the US Department of Commerce 's move is intended to force up the renminbi.
The spot exchange rate of the Chinese yuan against the US dollar rose above the 7.0 mark on the 23rd to close at 6.9961.
The midpoint of the officially regulated RMB exchange rate against the US dollar was cut by 17 basic points to 6.9938 on the 24th.
