Lewis family: John Lewis was a warrior "fighting for the weakest"
John Lewis, a member of the United States Congress and a civil rights fighter, was remembered as a warrior who "fought for the weakest" at a memorial service held for him on Saturday (July 25).
Lewis' public memorial service has been held in Alabama since Saturday.
There were two memorial services on the first day.
At the public memorial service at Troy University in Alabama on Saturday, Lewis' five siblings and one grandson spoke of him as a loving, afraid man who put his family first.
"He devoted his life to helping others," Henry "Grant" Lewis, Lewis's youngest brother, said during the meeting.
Samuel Lewis said his mother had warned John "not to get into trouble, not to go and get into trouble."
He added that John did not heed his mother's warning, saying, "We all know that John will always get into trouble and always get into trouble, but that is because he insists on the right thing, which is good trouble."
Lewis' brothers and sisters reminded the people at the memorial service that John 's most famous argument is to create "good trouble", that is, as long as it is for the sake of justice, he is not shy about stirring up trouble.
John once applied to Troy University, located in Troy, Alabama, his birthplace, but Troy University, which was then an all-white school, rejected his application for admission.
The John Lewis man, who preached the gospel to chickens on his farm as a child, went on to earn a degree in religion and philosophy from Fisk University.
Many years later, the University of Troy awarded Lewis an honorary doctorate.
Doug Jones, a congressional senator from Alabama, said that the current protesters "are protesting peacefully and nonviolently," just as Lewis did in the civil rights movement.
Jones said, "Even if President Trump turned over the boat and described all the protesters as thugs, he was wrong.
The protesters are patriots who want America to move toward a more equal country, "he said.
A six-day series of events in Lewis' honor will culminate this week at a funeral in Georgia.
On Saturday, Lewis' coffin was parked at a public memorial service at the University of Troy. People came to pay their respects to the civil rights pioneer.
Later on Saturday, a private service paid tribute to him in a chapel in Selma, Alabama, followed by a public tribute.
On Sunday, Lewis's body will pass the Edmund Pettus Bridge in Selma.
In 1965, he and the demonstrators demanding the right of blacks to vote were beaten by the Alabama police in front of the bridge. The police also fired tear gas at the demonstrators.
Lewis was nearly killed at the time.
After that day, it was known as "Bloody Sunday".
Lewis' body will be transported to Montgomery, the capital of Alabama.
Mayor Steven Reed encouraged people to line up on the sidewalk to join Lewis for this final ride.
At the same time, officials asked the public to wear masks and maintain social distance when participating in the event.
Alabama Gov. Kay Ivey ordered flags to be flown at half-staff on Saturday and Sunday in honor of Lewis.
During the nearly week-long commemoration, Lewis' body will be placed at the Alabama State Capitol in Montgomery, the Georgia State Capitol in Atlanta, and the United States Capitol in Washington for the public to pay their respects.
Nancy Pelosi, the speaker of the US House of Representatives, and Mitch McConnell, the majority leader of the Senate, announced last week that people can visit the US Capitol on Monday and Tuesday this year to pay their respects to Lewis.
Public tributes to Lewis will be held outdoors due to the coronavirus outbreak.
Shenzhen for public consultation on the introduction of health regulations - Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency, Shenzhen, July 26 (Reporters Mao Siqian and Bai Yu) encouraged residents to do medical examinations frequently and detect problems early; prohibited the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors; established an online game health examination system; employers should be equipped with full-time and part-time health managers... Recently, the Shenzhen Special Economic Zone Health Regulations (Exposure Draft) were officially released, and Shenzhen residents will have their own "health law".
In order to encourage residents to do medical examinations frequently and detect problems early, the above-mentioned consultation draft proposes that the health department should formulate a basic catalogue of health examination items according to different ages, occupations and other factors.
The cost of health examination that falls within the scope of the basic catalogue of health examination items shall be paid by the Social Medical Insurance Co-ordination Fund in accordance with the standard of once per person per year.
The consultation draft makes it clear that the employing unit shall rationally allocate human resources, arrange the bedtime of its employees, implement a rotation leave system for employees with heavy mental and manual labor loads, avoid excessive loss of human functions or physical and mental health injuries to the health of its employees, and strictly implement the paid leave system for its employees.
In addition, the employing unit shall provide full-time and part-time health managers and organize and carry out regular employee health check-ups.
In terms of the physical and mental health of minors, the consultation draft proposed that the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors should be prohibited, and that the location of the sale of alcoholic beverages should be restricted. Those who violate the regulations will be ordered by the market supervision and administration department to make corrections and fined 30,000 yuan.
In addition to "Prohibition of Alcohol", minors should also "exercise more".
According to the requirements of the consultation draft, the school should arrange more than one hour of physical activity for students every day.
For online games, the departments of public security, culture, radio, television, tourism and sports, network supervision, health and other departments should improve the health supervision system of Internet Internet service business premises, establish a health examination system for online games, and create a good communication space and communication culture for promoting the healthy growth of young people.
In addition, the consultation draft also proposed that influenza patients must wear masks when entering and leaving public places, and that medical and health institutions should be fined 20,000 yuan for divulging patients' privacy without consent.
It is worth noting that, in addition to the physical and mental health of residents, the consultation draft also requires that all departments in Shenzhen should assess the impact of the implementation of public policies on the health of the population before formulating plans and normative documents related to urban spatial planning and construction, industrial park planning and construction, resource exploitation and utilization and ecological environmental protection, the development of the biomedical industry, as well as approving major construction projects and implementing major public service projects.
If it has not been evaluated or will have a more serious adverse impact on urban public health or residents' health after evaluation, it shall not be formulated and promulgated or approved for implementation.
