Balance Bao income down "after 90" but "retaliatory" to save money?
With the decline of balance treasure income, "after 90" not only did not escape balance treasure, but began to "retaliate" to save money?
The "Saving Money After 90 Balance Bao" (2020 edition) recently released by the China New Economic Research Institute in conjunction with Alipay shows that in the first half of the year, the "post-90" became more fond of saving money: The amount of money saved per capita increased by nearly 40% over 2019.
Interestingly, "after 90" is more inclined to save from a "small amount of money", with 60% of the average amount of money saved is less than 20 yuan per sum...
Saving money with balance treasure has also become a saving habit in the "90s".
The data showed that of the 700 million balance treasure users, 134 million users are "after 90".
There are 174 million "after 90" in China, that is to say, about three out of every four "after 90" in the country are saving money with balance treasure.
At present, the seven-day annualized yield of money funds such as Balance Bao has slipped to about 1.5% from above 2% at the beginning of the year.
Even so, it did not affect the pace of saving money after the "90".
In the context of the improvement of the "saving effect" of balance treasure, many young people who are used to using balance treasure have also been directly transformed into "basic people".
Alipay data showed that as of July 13, the number of new "base people" on Alipay has more than doubled year-on-year in the past month, and more and more young people have achieved "advanced" financial management on Alipay.
Some analysts believe that the flow of funds from balance treasure into the stock market is also an important reason for the clear decline in the share of the IMF in June.
The report also showed that girls in the "90s" are more likely to save more money, on average 20% higher than boys. Of the users who hold funds on Alipay platform, 60% are men, and women tend to choose more robust financial management methods than men.
After saving money, what are the plans for the "90"?
Alipay data showed that "after 90" has the habit of saving money for the goal, with the largest number of users taking travel as the goal of saving money.
Affected by the epidemic, many "after 90" saved money to prepare for travel after the epidemic. The resumption of business in cinemas also provided a new way to shift from saving money to spending.
