Report says the shared accommodation market has picked up since March - CNN
This newspaper (reporter Yang Zhaokui) The "China Shared Accommodation Development Report 2020" (hereinafter referred to as the "Report") recently released by the Sharing Economic Research Center of the State Information Center shows that the transaction value of China's shared accommodation market fell 72.1% year-on-year in the first five months of 2020 due to the impact of the epidemic.
However, the shared accommodation market has recovered since March, and the market transaction value, order volume and reception number have gradually recovered.
The Report shows that the volume of transactions in the shared accommodation market has fallen sharply. On the one hand, it is due to the sharp decline in the demand for travel accommodation under the prevention and control of the epidemic, and the sharp decrease in the volume of orders. The total number of orders in the first five months fell by 65% year-on-year and the number of receptions fell by 63% year-on-year. On the other hand, the weakness of demand has also led to a more pronounced decline in overnight prices, with the average overnight price falling by 16% year-on-year in the first five months.
However, in March, April and May, the volume of market transactions increased by 78%, 199% and 35%, respectively. The number of orders increased by 141%, 152% and 50%, respectively. The number of visitors increased by 81%, 11% and 28%, respectively.
The Report pointed out that the development of the shared accommodation industry has been positive for a long time, but there are still many uncertainties in the near future.
In response, Yu Fengxia, deputy director of the Sharing Economy Research Center of the State Information Center, told the Workers' Daily that the development of shared accommodation needs stronger policy support. On the one hand, it is necessary to do a good job in the implementation of policies already in place in the previous period, further strengthen policy advocacy and pay attention to creating a better business environment. On the other hand, it is necessary to further strengthen policy guidance and support in terms of stimulating consumer demand, enriching the supply of tourism and residential services, innovating service methods and strengthening cooperation between the government and platform enterprises.
