Xiamen, July 26 (Yang Fushan Zhang Shushan Xu Jingyi) Vascular Surgery at Shanghai Changhai Hospital of Naval Military Medical University, the Famous Vascular Surgery Center of China, signed a contract with Zhongshan Hospital, affiliated with Xiamen University, on July 25 to jointly set up a collaborative center to promote exchanges and cooperation between the two sides in the field of vascular surgery, especially aortic acute and severe cases.
According to Zhongshan Hospital, affiliated with Xiamen University, after the vascular surgery of the two hospitals is formally formed into a collaborative unit, remote consultations will be carried out, treatment plans will be formulated for real-time online consultations with Changhai Hospital, talents will be selected for further education and training, and surgical technology exchanges, teaching and room inspections will be jointly carried out every week. For complex cases, Changhai experts can be invited to the hospital to perform surgery according to the needs of patients, thus realizing that patients in southwest Fujian can enjoy the top medical resources in the country without the province.
The two hospitals will also work together to carry out innovative scientific research on surgery, popularization of aortic diseases and early screening, among other things.
Sponsored by the Beijing Health Promotion Association and hosted by Zhongshan Hospital, affiliated with Xiamen University, a special aorta seminar was held in Xiamen on the same day.
At the same time at the meeting, the two well-known hospitals in Shanghai and Ha held the signing ceremony of the Vascular Surgery Collaborative Center and announced the formation of a collaborative unit to jointly improve the level of treatment of vascular surgery-related diseases in southwest Fujian.
Shanghai Changhai Hospital Vascular Surgery is the only Institute of Vascular Surgery in the army and the only clinical medical center for vascular system diseases in Shanghai. It is also the first national key discipline in vascular surgery. It has led the establishment of the Intracavity Vascular Science Professional Committee of the Chinese Medical Association and is a top team with deep accumulation in the industry.
Professor Huang Xiaojin, Director of Vascular Surgery, Zhongshan Hospital, affiliated with Xiamen University, gave an interview to the media.
Vascular surgery at Zhongshan Hospital, affiliated with Xiamen University, is the first independent vascular surgery in Fujian Province. It has long been committed to the diagnosis and treatment of aortic and peripheral blood tube diseases. In 2018, it was approved to build key clinical specialties at the provincial level.
In the treatment of aortic diseases, in addition to the treatment of dissection aneurysms and aortic aneurysms, he is experienced in emergency rupture of aortic aneurysms.
"Vascular surgery at Zhongshan Hospital, affiliated with Xiamen University, is outstanding in the region in terms of the history of development and the breadth, difficulty and complexity of surgery. Therefore, this time, we have set up a collaborative center. In addition to the aorta, we can also carry out all-round deep cooperation in medicine, teaching and scientific research in the diagnosis and treatment of lower limb arteries, carotid arteries and other diseases."
Professor Feng Rui, Deputy Director of Vascular Surgery at Shanghai Changhai Hospital, said.
Zhongshan Hospital, affiliated with Xiamen University, and Shanghai Changhai Hospital signed a contract in 2018 to set up the "Li Zhaoshen Famous Medical Studio" in the Department of Digestive Medicine.
Professor Huang Xiaojin, Director of Vascular Surgery at the hospital, told CNN that the hospital has also had a long history of exchanges with Changhai Hospital. This time, the two hospitals have officially formed a cooperative unit, bringing the cooperation and exchange between the two sides to a new level.
He said that the hospital will regularly invite Shanghai experts to the building to carry out surgical technology exchanges, teaching room inspections and difficult case discussions, while further carrying out remote consultations. At present, it plans to conduct remote consultations once a week. In addition, the department will select personnel for further study and exchange to strengthen the training and development of the subject talent team.
Reporters learned at the meeting that vascular disease is the number one cause of death in China, and the aorta, as the main route of all organs of the human body, flows from the heart to the whole body and plays an important role.
The occurrence of aortic diseases is often accompanied by high risk, high mortality rate and high difficulty of treatment. The thickest section of the aorta is 4cm in diameter. Once a hemangioma is formed, rupture occurs, or the endovascular rupture produces dissection, it will lead to heavy bleeding, which is very dangerous.
In recent years, with the change of people's lifestyle and the acceleration of the pace of life, China has become the largest country in the world for hypertension, and aortic diseases have also increased. Today, with the development of surgical technology and industrial materials, the treatment of aortic diseases has continued to develop in a minimally invasive, rapid and efficient direction.
Doctors can properly "change the channel" for blood flow by puncture from the thigh and placing a stent in the aorta, thus avoiding the impact on aneurysms or ruptured dissection and achieving good therapeutic results. Some operations even require only local anesthesia.
This academic seminar invited more than a dozen domestic experts to attend the meeting to discuss new advances in the treatment of aortic diseases, and to conduct cutting-edge technical training and difficult case discussions in the form of conference salons.
Reporters learned at the meeting that with the development of surgical technology and industrial materials, the current treatment of aortic diseases continues to develop in the direction of minimally invasive, rapid and efficient.
