Longest high-speed rail tunnel in the Three Gorges Reservoir Area is connected -- ScienceDaily
2020-07-26 17: 34: 48 Source: China News Network Author: Chen Haifeng Responsible Editor: Chen Haifeng
The picture shows the construction site of the Little Three Gorges Tunnel.
Supplied by China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Corporation
Chongqing, July 26 (Xinhua) -- A reporter from Han Lu learned from China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Co., Ltd., on July 26 that the Little Three Gorges Tunnel of the Zhengwan High Speed Rail, which is about 18.9 km long, was fully connected on the same day.
It is understood that the Little Three Gorges Tunnel is not only the longest high-speed rail tunnel within the Three Gorges Reservoir Area, but also the longest single-hole, two-lane high-speed rail tunnel designed to reach 350 km / h in projects currently under construction in China.
Located in the three provinces and cities of Henan, Hubei and Chongqing, the Zhengwan High Speed Rail connects the Beijing-Guangzhou and Xulan High Speed Rail to the north of Zhengzhou, and the Yuwan High Speed Rail to Chongqing in the south of Wanzhou. It is an important part of the riverside passageway and HuNantong Road in China's "eight vertical and eight horizontal" high-speed railway network.
The Little Three Gorges Tunnel of the Zhengwan High Speed Rail was fully connected on the 26th.
The picture shows the scene of the connection.
The Zhengwan high-speed railway starts in Zhengzhou City, Henan Province, and runs southwest through Pingdingshan City, Nanyang City, Xiangyang City, Hubei Province, to Wanzhou District, Chongqing City. The new line is about 818 km long, with a design speed of 350 km / h and about 184 km in Chongqing.
Among them, the Zhengzhou to Xiangyang section was opened for operation in advance on December 1, 2019, and the Chongqing section is stepping up its construction.
The Little Three Gorges Tunnel, which was fully connected on the 26th, is a full-line control project of the Zhengwan High Speed Rail. The project is located at the junction of Fengjie County and Wushan County in Chongqing. It is about 18.9 km long and has a maximum buried depth of 890 m.
Construction of the tunnel began in February 2017 and was fully connected on July 26, 2020.
According to Wang Jun, head of the design of the Zheng Wan High Speed Rail Tunnel of China China Railway Second Academy Engineering Group Co., Ltd., the survey and designer, the topographic and geological conditions of the location of the Little Three Gorges Tunnel are very complex and face risks such as karst, mud gushing and large deformation of soft rock. It is a Class I high-risk tunnel, which is extremely difficult to design and construct.
"During the construction of the project, we used geological survey method, geophysical exploration method and advanced drilling method to advance geological forecasting, and adopted special design schemes for more than 30 caves of various types. For example, we designed and built bridges 24 meters long, crossing large caves with a longitudinal length of more than 10 meters and a depth of more than 55 meters in the tunnel, so as to avoid tunnel settlement," the Royal Army said.
According to the China Railway Tunnel Bureau, the builder, the construction of the tunnel adopts a combination of diversion and blocking. By building horizontal hole flat guidance, grouting and water blocking, strengthening tunnel structural support and building sewage treatment stations, it not only ensures the orderly progress of the project, but also avoids the damage of construction drainage to the water body of the Little Three Gorges Scenic Area. At the same time, it successfully overcomes the construction problems such as adverse geology such as the large deformation of soft rock up to 7 kilometers long, and the maximum daily water inrush of 157,000 cubic meters.
When the entire Zhengwan high-speed railway line is completed and opened to traffic, it will become a new convenient and fast passenger main route from the Southwest region of China to the Central Plains, North China and Northeast regions. It is of great significance to improve the capacity and quality of the Northeast to railway corridor in the Southwest region, improve the layout of the regional road network, accelerate the development of tourism resources and urbanization along the route, promote the coordinated development of the region, and promote the implementation of the strategy for the development of the western region.
