Director Dapeng 's "Good Luck" was shortlisted for the Golden Jue Award - Xinhua
On July 18, the 23rd Shanghai International Film Festival announced the official list of films selected for the Golden Jue Award.
The first realistic film directed by Dapeng, "Good Luck", was successfully shortlisted for the Golden Jue Award at this festival. At the same time, the film officially released its first poster.
Picture of the poster
The film "Good Luck" is the first realistic work directed by Dapeng and his second tie with the Golden Jue Award.
The film tells the story of a comedy director who, on a whim, returned to his hometown in rural Northeast China, hoping to make a literary and artistic film about how the family made the Chinese New Year. As a result, he encountered a series of accidents.
The family members who gathered for making the film completed the final party.
In the film poster released today, Wang Jixiang, a member of the family, "Three Uncle", sits in the center of the picture smoking a cigarette. In the background, the black land of Northeast China, dressed in silver, is in the foreground. The red lantern that the Chinese must hang during the holidays is in the foreground.
The red lantern, which symbolizes festive and reunion, is in great contrast to Wang Jixiang, who is lonely, and seems to reveal the complexity and entanglements in the relationship between this extended family.
It is reported that in the film, except for the daughter of "Third Uncle" Wang Jixiang, who is played by actor Liu Lu, the rest of the play is completed by the real director's family. The experimental audio-visual style of the film breaks the boundary between drama and truth and brings the audience a new immersive viewing experience.
According to director Dapeng, the creation of "Good Luck" originated from "a providence". A series of sudden changes in the family during filming forced the original filming plan to be changed accordingly. Life without a script was eventually recorded as a film, but it released tension beyond design.
How on earth does director Dapeng face this "providence" and how should he continue to meet the changes brought about by this providence?
