Hunan Daily New Hunan Client July 25 (Our reporter) On July 25, two caravans carrying 5G new media mobile cloud broadcasting systems slowly drove out of the scene under the eyes of live guests, sponsored by the Financial Program Center of the Central Radio and Television Station, "Walking to the Village Live to See Poverty Alleviation", a large-scale integrated media operation.
General Secretary Xi Jinping pointed out that "2020 is a landmark year. We will build a well-off society in an all-round way and achieve the first century-old goal. 2020 will also be a decisive year in the decisive battle against poverty."
The large-scale financial media action "Walking to the Village Live to See Poverty Alleviation" is an important measure taken by the Financial Program Center of the Central Radio and Television Station to do a good job in publicizing the fight against poverty in line with this major theme.
The action will go into poverty eradication villages in more than 20 provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the Central Government throughout the country, excavate vivid poverty eradication stories, directly attack the great changes in the appearance of villages and villages, and show how villagers can break through the predicament of survival and development and move towards the road to becoming rich.
The operation will last for more than three months.
The reporter set out from Xuzhou. The soldiers took the Southwest Line in two ways, passing through Anhui, Hubei, Jiangxi, Hunan, Guangxi, Guizhou, Sichuan, Chongqing, Yunnan and Tibet. The other way, they took the Northwest Line, passing through Henan, Shaanxi, Gansu, Qinghai, Xinjiang, Ningxia, Inner Mongolia, Shanxi and Hebei, covering more than 10,000 kilometers.
In the form of reporting, "Walking to the Village Live to See Poverty Alleviation" is boldly integrated.
The economic development of the villages visited by the caravan will be broadcast through the CCTV Finance and Economics Channel of the Central Radio and Television Station, CCTV Economic Voice, China Traffic Broadcasting, CCTV Finance and New Media.
Among them, the live television broadcast will mainly be completed on CCTV Finance and Economics Channel 's midday news program, "World Finance" (premiere time: Monday to Sunday 12: 00 - 13: 00), and CCTV Finance and Economics Channel' s golden news program, "Economic Information Network", will open a poverty eradication report column (premiere time: Monday to Sunday 20: 30-21: 30).
At the same time, the caravan will broadcast each village it visits live on CCTV financial clients for up to one hour. Viewers can watch the live broadcast and participate in the raffle by downloading the CCTV financial APP.
In the application of technology and studio design, "Walking the Village Live to See Poverty Alleviation" has made a breakthrough and pioneered the "Outfield New Media Caravan".
The vehicle carries a new 5G media mobile cloud broadcasting system and uses 5G + 4K / 8K + AI technology to realize the organic combination of online and offline, large and small screens and television broadcasting.
The three-news broadcast area is equipped. The broadcast area is converted from a container. It is 12 meters long, 2.55 meters wide and 3.98 meters high. The box is equipped with a hydraulic automatic expansion structure, which can be turned up to 120 degrees.
The broadcast area can also be automatically expanded and connected to the external expansion platform, with an area of more than 50 square meters, which can meet the scene requirements of most programs.
At present, the Dongchuan District of Kunming City is already hot in summer, and what is hotter than the weather is the poverty alleviation workshop next to the relocation and resettlement site.
Lu Ling, an employee of Kunming Aisford Electronics Technology Company, said, "Now, as soon as you leave your home, you enter the factory door and make money to take care of your family, thanks to the free vocational skills training of the trade union organization."
Walking into the poverty alleviation workshop for the processing of electronic components in Tongdu Street, Dongchuan District, a busy picture of the heat came into view.
Lu Ling, who is in her 40s, is a single mother with children alone and has to take care of her elderly parents.
In her most difficult time, the Dongchuan District General Trade Union helped come up with ideas and ways to "give relief in the snow" after being busy before running.
Since 2018, Lu Ling has enjoyed assistance policies such as housing, schooling, social security and employment, as well as assistance funds issued by trade unions at all levels.
This year, her children have successfully graduated and taken up employment. She herself has a job and income after taking part in skills training. She got out of trouble at the end of April.
It is reported that the Dongchuan District General Organization is a special skills training project to help fight poverty, which is part of the skills training work of the Yunnan Provincial General Trade Union.
In the light of the characteristics of the workers in difficulty in the relocation and resettlement sites for poverty alleviation in the district, the district has conducted an in-depth investigation to understand the training needs and determine the training types. In the near future, it plans to train a total of 450 electricians, welders and noodle artists.
Recently, Li Yi, an employee of the Yunnan Menglian County branch of the Agricultural Bank, wrote a sincere thank-you letter to the county general trade union.
In her letter, she sincerely thanked her for the golden autumn student aid given to her by the union between August 2013 and January 2017, which helped her complete her studies.
In 2004, Li Yi 's father died in a car accident, and her mother was included in the file of workers in difficulty. Since then, she has been enjoying the care of the file card construction policy.
With the help of the local trade union, Li Yi successfully completed her studies.
Since 2016, 3809 households have been released from poverty through institutional guarantees and precise assistance.
The successful relief of the Lu Ling family and Li Yi is a microcosm of the Yunnan trade union 's promotion of the relief and relief work of workers in difficulty.
According to Duan Kaiyuan, a staff member of the Law and Rights Protection Work Department of the Yunnan General Trade Union, the province has always strengthened the dynamic management of the files of workers in difficulty, promoted the normalization of the filing work, and promptly included the assistance system for workers in difficulty who meet the conditions for filing. Broaden the application channels for workers in difficulty and use WeChat to open an online filing service platform for workers in difficulty to declare on their own initiative in a timely manner.
During the epidemic period, it was difficult to go out to work. In order to help the workers in difficulty ease the living pressure, Yunnan Province has allocated more than 13 million yuan in warm funds. In accordance with the standard of 2,000 yuan per family for the workers in difficulty at the national level and 1,500 yuan per family for the workers in difficulty at the provincial level, special warm condolence activities have been carried out for more than 6,000 families at the national level and more than 1,000 workers in difficulty at the provincial level.
At the same time, the provincial general has docked with various Internet recruitment platforms, such as the human society department and Zhilian recruitment, to push recruitment information to workers in difficulty, and to provide employment consultation, employment guidance and other services.
